# Security Enhancement Plan

## Goal
Strengthen authentication security to protect user data while maintaining a smooth, premium user experience ("invisible security").

## Current Status Analysis
- **Rating**: 8.5/10 (Strong Foundation)
- **Existing Protections**:
  - CSRF Protection (Standard Laravel)
  - Rate Limiting (5 attempts per minute)
  - Session Fixation protection
  - Bcrypt Hashing
  - Secure/HttpOnly Cookies

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> We are interpreting "complicated" as "Strict Security" for attackers, but we aim to keep it Simple for legitimate users.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Invisible Bot Protection (Honeypot)
Add an invisible input field to the Login/Register forms. Bots fill it out; humans don't. If filled, the request is rejected.
- **Impact**: zero friction for users, stops 90% of automated bots.

### 2. Strengthen Password Policy
Update `AppServiceProvider` to enforce stricter password rules globally.
- **Rule**: Minimum 10 characters, at least one number and symbol.
- **Impact**: Slightly harder cleanup, ensures stronger accounts.

### 3. Login Notification
Send an email "New Login Detected" if the IP address changes.
- **Impact**: High visibility for account takeover attempts.

### 4. Recaptcha v3 (Optional)
If bot attacks persist, we can add Google Recaptcha v3 which scores users without making them click cars/traffic lights.

#### [MODIFY] [AppServiceProvider.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/cavari/app/Providers/AppServiceProvider.php)
- Define default password rules: `min(10)->letters()->numbers()->symbols()`

#### [MODIFY] [auth-modal.blade.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/cavari/resources/views/components/auth-modal.blade.php)
- Add honeypot hidden field `gotcha`.

#### [MODIFY] [RegisteredUserController.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/cavari/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/RegisteredUserController.php)
- Add honeypot validation check before creating user.

#### [MODIFY] [AuthenticatedSessionController.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/cavari/app/Http/Controllers/Auth/AuthenticatedSessionController.php)
- Add honeypot validation check.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Attempt to register with weak password -> Expect Failure.
- Attempt to register/login with `gotcha` field filled -> Expect Failure.
- Attempt normal login -> Expect Success.
